  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model of CFD hemolysis prediction for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The surrogate was trained on high-fidelity CFD runs and validated against a held-out test set drawn from the same operating-condition distribution used during training. A note in the assessment states that real-world distribution shift is studied separately; no linked evidence for that study is provided. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
